An Ota Magistrates’ Court in Ogun on Tuesday sentenced a 26-year-old man, Femi Fayemi, to four years’ imprisonment for stealing a Bajaj motorcycle valued at N195,000. The Magistrate, Mr Matthew Akinyemim, sentenced Fayemi without an option of fine. Akinyemi convicted and sentenced Fayemi following his guilty plea to a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing, as well as the facts of the case. He said that the sentence would serve as a deterrent to crimes. ALSO READ: Xenophobia: South African policeman sentenced to 30 years for killing Nigerian Court restrains Kwara government from further demolition Court sentences househelp to one year in prison for stealing… Teenager in court for allegedly stealing 1m Man, 45, arraigned for allegedly receiving stolen goods Earlier, the Prosecutor, Insp. Abdulkareem Mustapha told the court that the defendant and others at large committed the offences on Dec. 31, 2019, at Goro Garage, Ijoko, Ota. Mustapha said that the accused and his accomplices conspired to steal the Bajaj motorcycle with registration number AGL 438 QH, belonging to the complainant, Mr Ismail Ibrahim. “The defendant was caught in the act by a vigilante group in the area which handed him over to the police,” he said. The prosecutor noted that the offences contravened Sections 390(9) and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ogun, 2006. (NAN) STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE